HEADWORD: malonylurea
<hw>malonylurea</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A white crystalline acid derived
from pyrimidine; it is used in preparing barbiturate drugs.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> barbituric acid.</syn>⟦br⟧
